          <h2>current news </h2>
          <h3>Lifting Working Group </h3><a name=section1></a>
          <p>Injuries arising from lifting operations  account for a significant proportion of the total of those occurring offshore;  typically about 20%.&nbsp; In response, the  IRF Lifting Working Group has formulated a regulatory strategy to address  worldwide lifting operations.&nbsp; The  strategy is due for implementation during 2007 and includes: 
            <ol type="a">
            <li> Inspection templates addressing:  Planning of lifting operations, Competency assurance, Maintenance, and Man  riding using winches.</li>
            <li> Recording of the root causes of  investigated incidents using a standardised methodology (Human, Technology,  Organisation) and</li>
            <li> A central database to collate worldwide  regulatory inspection and incident data.&nbsp;  Reports of the findings derived from the database will be published on  the IRF web site.&nbsp; <br />
              For further information contact <a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#105;&#97;&#105;&#110;&#46;&#112;&#97;&#116;&#101;&#114;&#115;&#111;&#110;&#64;&#104;&#115;&#101;&#46;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#46;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#46;&#117;&#107;&#32;">&#105;&#97;&#105;&#110;&#46;&#112;&#97;&#116;&#101;&#114;&#115;&#111;&#110;&#64;&#104;&#115;&#101;&#46;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#46;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#46;&#117;&#107;&#32;</a>
              </p>
            </li>
		    </ol>
            <h3>Performance Measurement Workgroup</h3><a name=section3></a>
          <p>The Performance Measurement Workgroup is a group formed by  members of the IRF, led by the US. The goal is:</p>
          <p>&lsquo;To measure and  compare offshore safety performance among IRF participants, by collecting and  comparing incident data based on a common set of criteria.&rsquo;</p>
          The work involves collecting incident data (fatalities, injuries, lost work time hours,  hydrocarbon and gas releases, collisions, fires and explosions) from all IRF  countries. A common set of criteria have been defined and data for 2004 and  2005 reworked to produce graphs giving an overview of how the industry is  performing. Work is continuing to collect additional data and refine the  normalisation process. A summary of the project so far is to be published on  the IRF website. For further  information on this Workgroup please contact  <a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#77;&#101;&#108;&#105;&#110;&#100;&#97;&#46;&#77;&#97;&#121;&#101;&#115;&#64;&#109;&#109;&#115;&#46;&#103;&#111;&#118;">&#77;&#101;&#108;&#105;&#110;&#100;&#97;&#46;&#77;&#97;&#121;&#101;&#115;&#64;&#109;&#109;&#115;&#46;&#103;&#111;&#118;</a></td>
